e a shot at killing Quill and snagging the cloak for yourself, that way when the Mage comes back you get to rub it in his/her face heh.<br><br>The same can be said for ANY class trying to get a much needed Epic piece, If you do not need it, cannot use it, then don't hog it!! If a Enchanter is going for their last epic piece, and it pops, there is no reason why a Cleric should be asking to roll for it!! If a Druid needs that last elusive thing and a Warrior in the group finds it, dont ransom the piece, turn the dam thing over!!<br><br>I am going to try again for the whole day, this Saturday the 16th with Widowmakr starting at 9am est....if i get screwed again and its not my fault, i will be back to the situation(s), just to show the rest of you how thoughtless and greedy some people can be!! So watch out!! ;-&quot;)<br><br>p.s. 2Kpp goes to anyone not from my guild who helps me bag the cloak as a gesture of my thanks for the time spent. seriously....i would offer more but thats all i have. <p>Magicks Gambit <BR><BR>ShadowKat Knytehunter Lvl 30 Vah Bst<Br>Widowmaker Soulstealer Lvl 30 Hum Mag<Br>SilverKat Mistpouncer Lvl 20 Hum Pal<Br><Br>*i am not twinked, i am just well equipted....er DoH*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utardaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tardaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/12/02 1:44:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1695.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mage Nuke</span><hr size=1> I see the horse up....it will die.  Then if the cloak does drop....I will MQ it will a mag who needs it and is of lvl to do the quest.  You talk of greed.....why would a lvl 30 mag need the cloak?  Can't do the rest of your quest for at least 16 lvls...